------security-entry------
-----security-entry------
------the_options-entry------
<font class="f-l">S</font>ince the system recognizes and builds an understanding of the information elements it is managing, enforcing security policies means:
<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;-  Defining the different security levels for the different types of elements:
<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;-  Based on what the elements contain and on existing security defined (acl) which (eventually) is sufficient to secure all elements found
<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;-  And/Or based on existing tags, labels, categories, assigned to the document, on ownership, location...
<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;-  Defining access security (down to person/document/record level) for each element type
<br/>
<font class="br_f-l">P</font>lus, based on the access security definitions, the system, when scanning the repositories, will automatically generate a Security Audit, for all the elements found.<div class='read_more'><a href='/a/aisca/read/'></a></div>

------the_options-entry------
-----the_options-entry------
-----request_form------
<font class="f-l">A</font>s it comes to data management & data processing, the logic behind the system and its fundamental building blocks make it infinitely flexible. So the options below just represent the most commonly modules, but the possibilities go as far as you wish to extend them.

<h2>Enterprise Data Consolidation</h2>
<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;-  Pan-Enterprise Search & Retrieval
<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;-  Archiving
<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;-  Policies Enforcements

<br/><br/>
<br/><h2>Content Management</h2>
<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;-  Self-Maintained Content Management System/Portal/Site (Intranet, Extra-net), Self-organizing, with the option to define Organization Rules
<br/><br/>
<br/><h2>Business Process Management</h2>
<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;-  Business Process Management through automatic Transactions Identification & Management, from defined Business Rules
<br/><br/>
<br/><h2>Web Content Management</h2>
<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;-  Web Content Management System/Portal/Site (Intranet, Extra-net)
<br/><br/>
<br/><h2>Web Information Portal (Intranet, Extra-net)</h2>
<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;-  Information Media Portal (Intranet, Extra-net)
<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;-  Consolidated Audio, Video, Image, Web Media Portal, with (automatic) Categorization, Labeling, Aggregation of Content, Automatic Hyper Linking...
<br/><br/>
<br/><h2>Sales & Marketing Site/Portal</h2>
<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;-  E-Commerce Catalog Site/Portal
<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;-  Consolidation of Sales & Marketing, E-Commerce Catalogs through (automatic) Categories creation, Product Categorization, Articles Federation...
<br/><br/>
<br/><h2>Knowledge Management Site/Portal</h2>
<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;-  Call/Help Center Site/Portal
<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;-  Consolidation of Existing Knowledge, Categorization, and Presentation as FAQ List, Automatic retrieval of Knowledge in Context for Call/Help Center Agents
<br/><br/>
<br/><h2>Legal Document Management System</h2>
<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;-  Digitalization, Consolidation of Legal Documents, Organization into Legal Structure, based Defined Hierarchical/Sensitivity Rules<div class='read_more'><a href='/a/aisca/read/'></a></div>



